<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4002411-katherine-gregg"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1561033479i/4002411._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4002411-katherine-gregg">Katherine Gregg</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">No, there aren&apos;t any images of the paintings in the book. I met the author recently at an event and he said that Jim Stegner is based on a real artist<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">No, there aren't any images of the paintings in the book. I met the author recently at an event and he said that Jim Stegner is based on a real artist named Jim Wagner out of Taos, NM. So you can google him and look at his artwork to get an idea of Stegner's paintings.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
