<span id="freeTextContainer15243944108559093285">This was a good read combining western vigilantism with an artistic flavour. The Painter is about a man- who is both a painter and fisherman -trying to escape the suffering of loss he has encountered in his life. Along that journey, however, he meets up with evil and decides to act on it taking the law into his own hands. His journey becomes one of being hunted and it&apos;s through this experience he is able to heal. The book is broken into canvases rather than chapters which was interesting. Very d</span>
  <span id="freeText15243944108559093285" style="display:none">This was a good read combining western vigilantism with an artistic flavour. The Painter is about a man- who is both a painter and fisherman -trying to escape the suffering of loss he has encountered in his life. Along that journey, however, he meets up with evil and decides to act on it taking the law into his own hands. His journey becomes one of being hunted and it's through this experience he is able to heal. The book is broken into canvases rather than chapters which was interesting. Very descriptive writing - was able to visualize each painting and the passion and emotion that each evoked. I give it 4 stars.</span>
