<div id="review_946937817" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/946937817" />
    <a title="Ann" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/406595-ann"><img alt="Ann" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1212144874p2/406595.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/946937817?book_show_action=true">May 24, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ann" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ann" href="/user/show/406595-ann">Ann</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer946937817" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10236254638685975291">And with this book, Peter Heller has placed himself firmly on my list of Favorite Living Authors. Beautiful, poetic, emotionally gut-wrenching. I underlined sentences. Oh, did I underline sentences! But this book goes well beyond pretty sentences. It has character. It has plot. And it has gorgeous, beautiful writing. It also has some wonderful meditations on art that I think hold true for writing as well.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


